		<comment>Up counter only INT values</comment>
		<attribute name="TypeDescriptiveForm" value="  This function block is used for counting INT values upward.  A &quot;1&quot; signal at the R input causes the value &quot;0&quot; to be assigned to the CV output.&#xA;  With each transition from &quot;0&quot; to &quot;1&quot; at the CU input, the value of CV is incremented by 1.&#xA;  When CV is &gt;= PV, the Q output is set to &quot;1&quot;.&#xA;&#xA;  Note: The counter only works to the maximum values of the data type being used.&#xA;        No overflow occurs.&#xA;&#xA;  This function block specification is defined in IEC 61131-3 and&#xA;  only works with the INT data type.&#xA;"></attribute>
		<attribute name="IsTypeHidden" value="FALSE"></attribute>
		<attribute name="IsTypeDiagnostic" value="FALSE"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeCodeCheckSumString" value="36F2"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeSignatureCheckSumString" value="6526"></attribute>
		<ExternalToolsOnly>
			<inputParameters>
				<variables name="CU" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Trigger input</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="1"></attribute>
					<attribute name="IsPinDiagnosticable" value="0"></attribute>
				</variables>
				<variables name="R" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Reset</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="2"></attribute>
					<attribute name="IsPinDiagnosticable" value="0"></attribute>
				</variables>
				<variables name="PV" typeName="INT">
					<comment>Preset value</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="3"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</inputParameters>
			<outputParameters>
				<variables name="Q" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Indicator output</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="1"></attribute>
				</variables>
				<variables name="CV" typeName="INT">
					<comment>Count value</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="3"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</outputParameters>
		</ExternalToolsOnly>
	</EFBSource>
	<EFSource nameOfEFType="INITCHART" version="1.00" dateTime="dt#2015-11-18-09:46:59">
		<comment>reset all active steps, standardises start of chart</comment>
		<attribute name="TypeDescriptiveForm" value="  This function is used to reset all active steps and standardises starts of charts.&#xA;  Danger: INITCHART should not be used for error detection on controllers for machine&#xA;          tools or, process or material handling systems when they are running.&#xA;          Failure to observe this precaution could result in death or serious injury.&#xA;&#xA;  Note: INITCHART has the highest priority of all EFs and EFBs controlling SFC charts.&#xA;&#xA;  If the input INIT_I=1, the chart is stopped and all active steps are reset.&#xA;  This situation is maintained as long as the input INIT_I is true.&#xA;  On a falling edge at INIT_I the chart will be started in standardized status.&#xA;  Output INIT_O will indicate this for one scan.&#xA;&#xA;  Note: Output INIT_O shows the actual state of the chart but the chart may also be&#xA;        started by EFB SFCCNTRL or some other command (externally).&#xA;"></attribute>
		<attribute name="IsTypeHidden" value="FALSE"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeCodeCheckSumString" value="0DBF"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeSignatureCheckSumString" value="E7F5"></attribute>
		<ExternalToolsOnly>
			<inputParameters>
				<variables name="CHARTREF" typeName="SFCCHART_STATE">
					<comment>Link to SFC-chart</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="1"></attribute>
				</variables>
				<variables name="INIT_I" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Reset and start a SFC Chart</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="2"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</inputParameters>
			<outputParameters>
				<variables name="INIT_O" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Show value of INIT_I in effect</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="2"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</outputParameters>
		</ExternalToolsOnly>
	</EFSource>
	<EFSource nameOfEFType="CLEARCHART" version="1.00" dateTime="dt#2015-11-18-09:46:59">
		<comment>Reset all active steps of a SFC Chart</comment>
		<attribute name="TypeDescriptiveForm" value="  This function is used to reset all active steps.&#xA;  Danger: CLEARCHART should not be used for error detection on controllers for machine&#xA;          tools or, processing or material handling systems when they are running.&#xA;          Failure to observe this precaution could result in death or serious injury.&#xA;&#xA;  If a rising edge at CLEAR_I is detected, all active steps will be stopped and reset.&#xA;  This status is maintained as long as the input CLEAR_I is true. It will even be maintained after&#xA;  setting CLEAR_I to false. The situation is shown at the output (CLEAR_O = 1).&#xA;&#xA;  Once CLEAR_I is set to 0, the steps can be activated by the EFB SFCCNTRL (input INIT),&#xA;  the function INITCHART or some other step-activation command (externally).&#xA;&#xA;  Note: Output CLEAR_O shows the actual state of the chart. It may be reset by EFB SFCCNTRL,&#xA;        the function INITCHART, the procedure RESETSTEP or some other command (externally).&#xA;"></attribute>
		<attribute name="IsTypeHidden" value="FALSE"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeCodeCheckSumString" value="F9F1"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeSignatureCheckSumString" value="E9CE"></attribute>
		<ExternalToolsOnly>
			<inputParameters>
				<variables name="CHARTREF" typeName="SFCCHART_STATE">
					<comment>Link to SFC-chart</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="1"></attribute>
				</variables>
				<variables name="CLEAR_I" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>0-&gt;1: Reset a SFC Chart</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="2"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</inputParameters>
			<outputParameters>
				<variables name="CLEAR_O" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Chart was reset, no active step</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="2"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</outputParameters>
		</ExternalToolsOnly>
	</EFSource>
	<EFBSource nameOfEFBType="TON" version="1.00" dateTime="dt#2015-11-18-09:16:02">
		<comment>On delay</comment>
		<attribute name="TypeDescriptiveForm" value="  The function block is used as the On delay.  When the function block is called for the first time, the initial state of ET is &quot;0&quot;.&#xA;"></attribute>
		<attribute name="IsTypeHidden" value="FALSE"></attribute>
		<attribute name="IsTypeDiagnostic" value="FALSE"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeCodeCheckSumString" value="B257"></attribute>
		<attribute name="TypeSignatureCheckSumString" value="16D2"></attribute>
		<ExternalToolsOnly>
			<inputParameters>
				<variables name="IN" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Start delay</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="1"></attribute>
					<attribute name="IsPinDiagnosticable" value="0"></attribute>
				</variables>
				<variables name="PT" typeName="TIME">
					<comment>Preset delay time</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="2"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</inputParameters>
			<outputParameters>
				<variables name="Q" typeName="BOOL">
					<comment>Delayed output</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="1"></attribute>
				</variables>
				<variables name="ET" typeName="TIME">
					<comment>Internal time</comment>
					<attribute name="PositionPin" value="2"></attribute>
				</variables>
			</outputParameters>
		</ExternalToolsOnly>
	</EFBSource>
